ory:Expatriate footballers in Romania]]\n[[Category:Uruguayan expatriate sportspeople in Argentina]]\n[[Category:Uruguayan expatriate sportspeople in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Uruguayan expatriate sportspeople in Romania]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Montevideo]]\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Danubio F.C. managers]]\n\n\n{{uruguay-footy-defender-1980s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Uruguayan footballer}}\n{{for|the Argentine Olympic fencer|Marcelo M\u00e9ndez (fencer)}}\n{{Spanish name|M\u00e9ndez|Russo}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name          = Marcelo M\u00e9ndez\n| fullname            = Marcelo Fabi\u00e1n M\u00e9ndez Russo\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1981|1|10|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Montevideo]], [[Uruguay]]\n| height              = 1.85 m\n| position            = [[Defender (association football)|Central back]]\n| currentclub         = \n| clubnumber          = \n| youthyears1         = \n| youthclubs1         = \n| years1              = 2000\u20132004 | clubs1  = [[Centro Atl\u00e9tico F\u00e9nix|F\u00e9nix]] | caps1  = 31 | goals1  = 1\n| years2              = 2005 | clubs2  = [[Atl\u00e9tico Junior]] | caps2  = 9| goals2  = 0\n| years3              = 2005\u20132006 | clubs3  = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Independiente|Independiente]] | caps3  = 24 | goals3  = 0\n| years4              = 2006\u20132007 | clubs4  = [[Kayserispor]] | caps4  = 26 | goals4  = 2\n| years5              = 2007 | clubs5  = [[C.A. Pe\u00f1arol|Pe\u00f1arol]] | caps5  = 16 | goals5  = 0\n| years6              = 2008 | clubs6  = [[Atl\u00e9tico Junior]] | caps6  = 12 | goals6  = 0\n| years7              = 2009 | clubs7  = [[Montevideo Wanderers F.C.|Montevideo Wanderers]] | caps7  = 15 | goals7 = 3\n| years8              = 2010 | clubs8  = [[FC Astra|Astra]] | caps8  = 8 | goals8  = 0\n| years9              = 2010\u20132011 | clubs9  = [[Independiente Rivadavia]] | caps9  = 11 