t Goldfaden on line]\n* [http://findingaids.cjh.org/?pID=1358886 Abraham Goldfaden Collection] at the [[YIVO]] Institute for Jewish Research, NY\n* Free song lyrics in Yiddish and sheet music by Abraham Goldfaden http://ulrich-greve.eu/free/goldfaden.html\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Goldfaden, Abraham}}\n[[Category:1840 births]]\n[[Category:1908 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Starokostiantyniv Raion]]\n[[Category:People from Volhynian Governorate]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian Jews]]\n[[Category:Imperial Russian emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:American people of Ukrainian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Yiddish-language writers]]\n[[Category:Translators to Yiddish]]\n[[Category:Yiddish-language playwrights]]\n[[Category:Hebrew-language playwrights]]\n[[Category:Yiddish theatre performers]]\n[[Category:Yiddish theatre]]\n[[Category:Hazzans]]\n[[Category:20th-century translators]]\n[[Category:19th-century Russian dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:19th-century translators]]\n[[Category:20th-century Russian dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:19th-century Russian singers]]\n[[Category:Jewish Ukrainian actors]]\n", "name_user": "Hilmorel", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBucharest", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abraham_Goldfaden"}
{"title_page": "Nick Millington", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n|name                = Nick Millington\n|image               = Nicholas MILLINGTON.jpg\n|image_size          = 200\n|caption             = Nick Millington with the U.S. U17 national team\n|fullname            = Nicholas Stephen Millington\n|birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1991|8|9}}\n|birth_place         = [[Hartford, Connecticut]], United States\n|height              = {{height|m=1.75}}\n|position            = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]], [[Midfielder]]\n|currentclub         =\n|clubnumber          = \n|youthyears1         = 2005\u20132006\n|youthclubs1         = [[Raleigh CASL Elite]]\n|youthyears2         = 2006\u20132008\n|youthclubs2         = [[IMG Soccer Academy]]\n|youthyears3         = 2008\u20132009\n|youthclubs3         = [[Wake Forest Demon Deacons men's soccer|Wake Forest Demon Deacons]]\n|youthyears4         = 2010\u20132011\n|youthclubs4         = [[Elon Phoenix]]\n|years1              = 2009\n|clubs1              = [[Cary Clarets]]\n|caps1               = 6\n|goals1              = 1\n|years2              = 2012\u20132014\n|clubs2              = [[Carolina RailHawks]]\n|caps2               = 32\n|goals2              = 0\n|nationalyears1      = 2006\u20132007\n|nationalteam1       = [[United States men's national under-17 soccer team|United States U17]]\n|nationalcaps1       = 11\n|nationalgoals1      = 0\n|nationalyears2      = 2008\u20132009\n|nationalteam2       = [[United States men's national under-18 soccer team|United States U18]]\n|nationalcaps2       = 11\n|nationalgoals2      = 0\n|nationalyears3      = 2012\n|nationalteam3       = [[Guyana national football team|Guyana]]\n|nationalcaps3       = 6\n|nationalgoals3      = 0\n|medaltemplates      = \n|club-update         = December 13, 2014\n|nationalteam-update = December 13, 2014\n}}\n'''Nicholas Stephen \"Nick\" Millington''' (born August 9, 1991) is a retired American-born Guyanese [[association football|footballer]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Youth, College and Amateur===\nAfter spending time with [[Raleigh CASL Elite]] and the U.S. Soccer Residency program, Millington signed to play at [[Wake Forest University]].  In this freshman year in 2008, Millington made 13 appearances including one starts and finished the year with a goal and an assist.  \n\nAfter making 14 appearances for Wake Forest in 2009, Millington transferred to [[Elon University]] where he saw more playing time, starting 16 of 17 matches in 2010 and scoring one goal.  In 2011, he made 21 appearances and finished with a goal and two assists.\n\nMillington also spent the 2009 season with the [[Cary Clarets]] in the [[USL Premier Development League]].<ref>{{cite news |title=2009 Cary Clarets stats |url=http://www.uslsoccer.com/teams/2009/6188469.html#STATS |work=uslsoccer.com |publisher=United Soccer Leagues |accessdate=29 June 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100105203217/http://www.uslsoccer.com/teams/2009/6188469.html#STATS |archivedate=5 January 2010 }}</ref>\n\n===Professional===\nOn May 18, 2012, Millington signed his first professional contract, joining [[North American Soccer League|NASL]] club [[Carolina RailHawks FC|Carolina RailHawks]].<ref name=\"nick_millington\">{{cite news |title=RailHawks add defensive players to roster |url=http://www.nasl.com/index.php?id=3&newsid=2314 |work=North American Soccer League |publisher=NASL |date=18 May 2012 |accessdate=29 June 2012 }}</ref>  He made his professional debut on June 2 in a 2-1 win over the [[Puerto Rico Islanders]].<ref>http://www.nasl.com/index.php?id=488&getGameID=175</ref>\n\n===International===\nMillington spent time with both the U.S. U17 and U18 national teams.<ref name=\"nick_millington\"/>  On August 13, 2012, Millington was called up by the [[Guyana national football team|Guyanese national team]] for their international friendly match against [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]].<ref>{{cite news |title=RailHawks Players Join National Team for International Friendlies |url=http://www.nasl.com/index.php?id=3&newsid=3036 |work=North American Soccer League |publisher=NASL |date=13 August 2012 |accessdate=15 August 2012 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{NFT player|pid=48359}}\n* [http://www.elonphoenix.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=2128 Elon University bio]\n* [http://www.ussoccer.com/teams/u-18-mnt/m/nick-millington.aspx U.S. Soccer profile]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Millington, Nick}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American soccer players]]\n[[Category:Guyanese footballers]]\n[[Category:Guyana international footballers]]\n[[Category:Wake Forest Demon Deacons men's soccer players]]\n[[Category:Elon Phoenix men's soccer players]]\n[[Category:Cary Clarets players]]\n[[Category:North Carolina FC players]]\n[[Category:American people of Guyanese descent]]\n[[Category:USL League Two players]]\n[[Category:North American Soccer League players]]\n[[Category:United States men's youth international soccer players]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n\n\n{{US-footy-bio-stub}}\n{{Guyana-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n|name                = Nick Millington\n|image               = Nicholas MILLINGTON.jpg\n|image_size          = 200\n|caption             = Nick Millington with the U.S. U17 national team\n|fullname            = Nicholas Stephen Millington\n|birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1991|8|9}}\n|birth_place         = [[Hartford, Connecticut]], United States\n|height              = {{height|m=1.75}}\n|position            = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]], [[Midfielder]]\n|currentclub         =\n|clubnumber          = \n|youthyears1         = 2005\u20132006\n|youthclubs1         = [[Raleigh CASL Elite]]\n|youthyears2         = 2006\u20132008\n|youthclubs2         = [[IMG Soccer Academy]]\n|youthyears3         = 2008\u20132009\n|youthclubs3         = [[Wake Forest Demon Deacons men's soccer|Wake Forest Demon Deacons]]\n|youthyears4         = 2010\u20132011\n|youthclubs4         = [[Elon Phoenix]]\n|years1              = 2009\n|clubs1              = [[Cary Clarets]]\n|caps1               = 6\n|goals1              = 1\n|years2              = 2012\u20132014\n|clubs2              = [[Carolina RailHawks]]\n|caps2               = 32\n|goals2              = 0\n|nationalyears1      = 2006\u20132007\n|nationalteam1       = [[United States men's national under-17 soccer team|United States U17]]\n|nationalcaps1       = 11\n|nationalgoals1      = 0\n|nationalyears2      = 2008\u20132009\n|nationalteam2       = [[United States men's national under-18 soccer team|United States U18]]\n|nationalcaps2       = 11\n|nationalgoals2      = 0\n|nationalyears3      = 2012\n|nationalteam3       = [[Guyana national football team|Guyana]]\n|nationalcaps3       = 6\n|nationalgoals3      = 0\n|medaltemplates      = \n|club-update         = December 13, 2014\n|nationalteam-update = December 13, 2014\n}}\n'''Nicholas Stephen \"Nick\" Millington''' (born August 9, 1991) is a retired American-born Guyanese [[association football|footballer]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Youth, College and Amateur===\nAfter spending time with [[Raleigh CASL Elite]] and the U.S. Soccer Residency program, Millington signed to play at [[Wake Forest University]].  In this freshman year in 2008, Millington made 13 appearances including one starts and finished the year with a goal and an assist.  After making 14 appearances for Wake Forest in 2009, Millington transferred to [[Elon University]] where he saw more playing time, starting 16 of 17 matches in 2010 and scoring one goal.  In 2011, he made 21 appearances and finished with a goal and two assists.\n\nMillington also spent the 2009 season with the [[Cary Clarets]] in the [[USL Premier Development League]].<ref>{{cite news |title=2009 Cary Clarets stats |url=http://www.uslsoccer.com/teams/2009/6188469.html#STATS |work=uslsoccer.com |publisher=United Soccer Leagues |accessdate=29 June 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100105203217/http://www.uslsoccer.com/teams/2009/6188469.html#STATS |archivedate=5 January 2010 }}</ref>\n\n===Professional===\nOn May 18, 2012, Millington signed his first professional contract, joining [[North American Soccer League|NASL]] club [[Carolina RailHawks FC|Carolina RailHawks]].<ref name=\"nick_millington\">{{cite news |title=RailHawks add defensive players to roster |url=http://www.nasl.com/index.php?id=3&newsid=2314 |work=North American Soccer League |publisher=NASL |date=18 May 2012 |accessdate=29 June 2012 }}</ref>  He made his professional debut on June 2 in a 2-1 win over the [[Puerto Rico Islanders]].<ref>http://www.nasl.com/index.php?id=488&getGameID=175</ref>\n\n===International===\nMillington spent time with both the U.S. U17 and U18 national teams.<ref name=\"nick_millington\"/>  On August 13, 2012, Millington was called up by the [[Guyana national football team|Guyanese national team]] for their international friendly match against [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]].<ref>{{cite news |title=RailHawks Players Join National Team for International Friendlies |url=http://www.nasl.com/index.php?id=3&newsid=3036 |work=North American Soccer League |publisher=NASL |date=13 August 2012 |accessdate=15 August 2012 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{NFT player|pid=48359}}\n* [http://www.elonphoenix.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=2128 Elon University bio]\n* [http://www.ussoccer.com/teams/u-18-mnt/m/nick-millington.aspx U.S. Soccer profile]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Millington, Nick}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American soccer players]]\n[[Category:Guyanese footballers]]\n[[Category:Guyana international footballers]]\n[[Category:Wake Forest Demon Deacons men's soccer players]]\n[[Category:Elon Phoenix men's soccer players]]\n[[Category:Cary Clarets players]]\n[[Category:North Carolina FC players]]\n[[Category:American people of Guyanese descent]]\n[[Category:USL League Two players]]\n[[Category:North American Soccer League players]]\n[[Category:United States men's youth international soccer players]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n\n\n{{US-footy-bio-stub}}\n{{Guyana-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Infogapp1", "label": "safe", "comment": "space", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nick_Millington"}
{"title_page": "Ilkka M\u00e4kel\u00e4", "text_new": "{{short description|Finnish football manager, former player, and coach}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Ilkka M\u00e4kel\u00e4\n| image               =\n| fullname            =\n| height              =\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1963|6|25}}\n| birth_place         = [[Elim\u00e4ki]], [[Finland]]\n| currentclub         = [[Myllykosken Pallo \u221247|MyPa]] (Manager)\n| clubnumber          =\n| position            = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| years1 = \u20131982 | years2 = 1983 | years3 = 1984 | years4 = 1985\u20131989 | years5 = 1988 | years6 = 1990\u20131996 | years7 = 1997\u20131999 | years8 = 2000 | years9 =2001\u20132003\n| clubs1 = [[Mikkelin Palloilijat|MP]] | clubs2 = [[FC Lahti|FC Kuusysi]] | clubs3 = [[Mikkelin Palloilijat|MP]] | clubs4 = [[FC Haka]] | clubs5 = [[FC Wettingen]] | clubs6 = [[Mikkelin Palloilijat|MP]] | clubs7 = [[RoPS]] | clubs8 = [[FC Lahti]] | clubs9 =[[MYPA]]\n| caps1 = ? | goals1 = ? | caps2 = 27 | goals2 = 12 | caps3 = 22 | goals3 = 7 | caps4 = 98 | goals4 = 13 | caps5 = ? | goals5 = ? | caps6 = 159 | goals6 = 7 | caps7 = 77 | goals7 = 2 | caps8 = 27 | goals8 = 0 | caps9 = 7 | goals9 = 0\n| nationalyears1=| nationalyears2 = \n| nationalteam1 = [[Finland national under-21 football team|Finland U-21]] | nationalteam2 =[[Finland national football team|Finland]]<ref>http://www.jalkapallovalmentajat.fi/yhteystiedot/ilkka_makela/</ref>\n| nationalcaps1 = 15 | nationalgoals1 = ? | nationalcaps2 = 11 | nationalgoals2 = 0\n| manageryears1 = 2001\u20132003\n| manageryears2 = 2004\u20132007\n| manageryears3 = 2008\u20132010\n| manageryears4 = 2011\u20132013\n| manageryears5 = 2011\u20132013\n| manageryears6 = 2011\u20132013\n| manageryears7 = 2015\u20132017\n| manageryears8 = 2020\u2013\n| managerclubs1 = [[Myllykosken Pallo \u221247|MyPa]] (player-assistant)\n| managerclubs2 = [[Myllykosken Pallo \u221247|MyPa]]\n| managerclubs3 = [[FC Lahti]]\n| managerclubs4 = [[Finland national under-15 football team|Finland U15]]\n| managerclubs5 = [[Finland national under-16 football team|Finland U16]]\n| managerclubs6 = [[Finland national under-17 football team|Finland U17]]\n| managerclubs7 = [[Mikkelin Palloilijat]]\n| managerclubs8 = [[Myllykosken Pallo \u221247|MyPa]]\n}}\n\n'''Ilkka M\u00e4kel\u00e4''' (born 25 June 1963, in [[Elim\u00e4ki]]) is a [[Finland|Finnish]] [[football (soccer)|football]] manager, former player, and current manager of [[Myllykosken Pallo \u221247|MyPa]].\n\n==Coaching career==\nHe was sacked after the [[2010 Veikkausliiga|2010 season]] as FC Lahti were relegated to [[Ykk\u00f6nen]]. On 20 December 2010 he signed a three-year contract with Finnish FA, taking the Finland's U15, U16 and U17 teams under his management.<ref>[http://www.mtv3.fi/urheilu/futis/uutiset.shtml/arkistot/futis/2010/12/1244545 M\u00e4kel\u00e4 takes charge at Finland youth] {{in lang|fi}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 November 2019 [[Myllykosken Pallo \u221247|MyPa]] confirmed, that M\u00e4kel\u00e4 would return as the clubs manager for the 2020 season.<ref>[https://www.mypa.fi/uutiset/ilkka-makela-on-mypan-uusi-paavalmentaja Ilkka M\u00e4kel\u00e4 on MYPAn uusi p\u00e4\u00e4valmentaja], mypa.fi, 19 November 2019</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.webcitation.org/5hX7vE8Xu?url=http://www.veikkausliiga.com/ennatykset_index.htm Veikkausliiga Hall of Fame]\n*{{FootballDatabase.eu|192925<!-- -ilkka-makela -->}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2011}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Makela, Ilkka}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Finnish footballers]]\n[[Category:Finnish football managers]]\n[[Category:Veikkausliiga players]]\n[[Category:Finnish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Finland international footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Haka players]]\n[[Category:Rovaniemen Palloseura players]]\n[[Category:FC Lahti players]]\n[[Category:Myllykosken Pallo \u221247 players]