m Lopez\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2004\u20132006\n| ''[[Missing (Canadian TV series)|Missing]]''\n| Antonio Cortez\n| 37 episodes<br>Nominated\u2014[[Imagen Awards|Imagen Award for Best Supporting Actor on Television]]\n|-\n| 2005\u20132006\n| ''[[Hope & Faith]]''\n| Gary Gucharez\n| 10 episodes\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]]''\n| US Attorney Berner\n| Episode: \"Albatross\"\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Age of Love (TV series)|Age of Love]]''\n| Himself / Host\n| 8 episodes\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Ugly Betty]]''\n| Detective Averaimo\n| Episode: \"Crimes of Fashion\"\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[The Protector (American TV series)|The Protector]]''\n| Chuck Wyatt\n| Episode: \"Bangs\"\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[I Hate My Teenage Daughter]]''\n| Alejandro Castillo\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]''\n| Matt Martinez\n| Episode: \"Justice Denied\"\n|-\n| 2012\u20132013\n| ''[[American Horror Story: Asylum]]''\n| Spivey\n| 5 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[The New Normal (TV series)|The New Normal]]''\n| Chris\n| Episode: \"Gaydar\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Guys with Kids]]''\n| Andy\n| Episode: \"The Will\"\n|-\n| 2013\u20132014\n| ''[[Alpha House]]''\n| Andy Guzman\n| 21 episodes \n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Kingdom (2014 TV series)|Kingdom]]''\n| Sean Chapas\n| 5 episodes\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Pitch (TV series)|Pitch]]''\n| Oscar\n| 10 episodes \n|-\n| 2016\n|''[[Queen of the South (TV series)|Queen of the South]]\n| Teo Aljarafe\n| 7 episodes \n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Difficult People]]''\n| Joey \n| Episode: \"Italian Pi\u00f1ata\"\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Nightcap (2016 TV series)|Nightcap]]''\n| Himself\n| Episode: \"Babymaker\"\n|-\n| 2017\u2013present\n| ''[[Riverdale (2017 TV series)|Riverdale]]''\n| [[Hiram Lodge]]\n| 50 episodes<br>[[Teen Choice Award for Choice TV Villain]]\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[The Night Shift (TV series)|The Night Shift]]''\n| Dr. Cain Diaz\n| 8 episodes\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Broad City]]''\n| Brad\n| Episode: \"Bitcoin & the Missing Girl\"\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0176175|Mark Consuelos}}\n{{Teen Choice Award Choice TV Villain}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Consuelos, Mark}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:American male actors of Mexican descent]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American male soap opera actors]]\n[[Category:American people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Hispanic and Latino American male actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Military brats]]\n[[Category:Spanish emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:University of South Florida alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Zaragoza]]\n[[Category:People from Lebanon, Illinois]]\n[[Category:People from the Upper East Side]]\n[[Category:People from SoHo, Manhattan]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actor|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Mark Consuelos\n| image              = Mark Consuelos by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| caption            = Consuelos in 2018\n| birth_name         = Mark Andrew Consuelos\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1971|3|30}}\n| birth_place        = [[Zaragoza]], [[Francoist Spain|Spain]]\n| education          = [[Bloomingdale High School]]\n| alma_mater         = [[University of South Florida]]\n| nationality        = American\n| children           = 3\n| homepage           = \n| spouse             = {{marriage|[[Kelly Ripa]]|1996}}\n}}\n'''Mark Andrew Consuelos''' (born March 30, 1971)<ref name=birthdate>{{cite web| url=http://www.eonline.com/news/641936/mark-consuelos-reveals-44th-birthday-present-from-wife-kelly-ripa-calls-it-the-best-gift-i-ve-ever-received| title=Mark Consuelos Reveals 44th Birthday Present From Wife Kelly Ripa, Calls It ''the Best Gift I've Ever Received''|first=Alyssa|last=Toomey| publisher=[[E! News]]| date= April 1, 2015|accessdate= March 6, 2017|archivedate=April 3, 2015 | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20150403002530/http://www.eonline.com/news/641936/mark-consuelos-reveals-44th-birthday-present-from-wife-kelly-ripa-calls-it-the-best-gift-i-ve-ever-received | url-status=live|quote='My wife got me a plaque on one of the park benches.' The [birthday-present] plaque read 'Daddy Cool, est. March 30, 1971,' and as Consuelos explained, 'That's what she calls me. ...That's the best gift I've ever received.'}}</ref> is an American actor. He is best known for his portrayal of [[Mateo Santos]] on the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] soap opera ''[[All My Children]]'' (1995\u20132001; 2010) and supporting actor [[Hiram Lodge]] on [[The CW]] drama ''[[Riverdale (2017 TV series)|Riverdale]]'' (2017\u2013present).\n\n==Early life==\nMark Consuelos<ref name=\"nbcbio\">{{cite news | title = Mark Consuelos |publisher=Age of Love official website (NBC) | url = http://www.nbc.com/Age_of_Love/bios/bio_host.shtml | accessdate = September 10, 2007| archivedate= June 13, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070613123030/http://www.nbc.com/Age_of_Love/bios/bio_host.shtml}}</ref> was born in [[Zaragoza]], [[Francoist Spain|Spain]], to an Italian mother, Camilla, and a Mexican father, Saul Consuelos.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/sptimes/access/22788377.html?dids=22788377:22788377&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Feb+25%2C+1996&author=ACE+ATKINS&pub=St.+Petersburg+Times&desc=TV+role+brings+dream+to+life&pqatl=google | work=St. Petersburg Times | title=TV role brings dream to life | first=Ace | last=Atkins | date=February 25, 1996}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/mark-consuelos/bio/192015 |title=Mark Consuelos Biography, Celebrity Facts and Awards |magazine=TV Guide |date=January 29, 2018 |accessdate=March 27, 2018}}</ref> He is the youngest of three children: he has one brother, a doctor, and one sister, a lawyer. Consuelos has lived in Italy and the United States since childhood.  He grew up in [[Lebanon, Illinois]], and later in [[Brandon, Florida]].<ref name=\"nbcbio\"/> He attended [[Bloomingdale High School]] in [[Valrico, Florida]], and then went to [[University of Notre Dame]] before transferring to and graduating from the [[University of South Florida]] with a degree in marketing in 1994.<ref name=\"abcbio\">{{cite news | title = Mark Consuelos|work=ABC | url = http://www.wchstv.com/abc/allmychildren/markconsuelos.shtml | accessdate = September 10, 2007 }}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nConsuelos had a starring role in the educational serial ''[[Connect With English]]'', which aired on public television stations as part of the [[Annenberg/CPB Project]].{{Citation needed|date=December 2009}}\n\nIn February 1995, Consuelos had his breakthrough when he landed the role of [[Mateo Santos]] on the soap opera ''[[All My Children]]''.<ref name=\"nbcbio\"/> There, he fell in love with his on-screen [[love interest]] [[Kelly Ripa]], and secretly married her in Las Vegas, in May 1996. At the time, he lived on co-star [[Winsor Harmon]]'s sofa; Harmon was one of the few to know that co-stars Ripa and Consuelos were not only dating, but married.\n\nRipa and Consuelos continued to tape episodes of ''All My Children'' until 2002, when Ripa wished to focus more on her other job: taking over for [[Kathie Lee Gifford]] as host of what then became  ''[[Live with Regis and Kelly|Live! with Regis and Kelly]]'' (later known as ''[[Live! with Kelly]]'', and subsequently as ''[[Live! with Kelly and Michael]]'' and even later became \"[[Live with Kelly and Ryan]]\"). Consuelos is a regular guest co-host.\n\nSince leaving ''All My Children'', Consuelos has starred in the feature film ''[[The Great Raid]]'', which debuted in theatres in 2005. In 2006, he appeared in the movies ''[[My Super Ex-Girlfriend]]'', as Steve, and ''[[Wedding Daze]]''.<ref name=\"nbcbio\" /> He has been seen on the [[Lifetime Television|Lifetime]] series ''[[1-800-Missing|Missing]]'', with [[Vivica A. Fox]].<ref name=\"nbcbio\" /> He also had a part in ''[[Ugly Betty]]''.\n\nConsuelos hosted two reality dating shows, ''[[Age of Love (TV series)|Age of Love]]''<ref name=\"nbcbio\"/> and ''[[Science of Love]]'', both airing on [[NBC]] in 2007. He guest-starred on ''[[Third Watch]]'', ''[[Friends]]'', ''American Family,'' ''Fortune Hunter'', ''[[SeaQuest]]'' and ''[[Hope & Faith]]''.<ref name=\"nbcbio\"/>\n\nA weekly live episode of the ''Oprah Winfrey Show'' premiered in the show's 23rd season with a panel consisting of Mark Consuelos, Ali Wentworth, Oprah Winfrey, and Gayle King. The panel discussed the week's news and highlighted events in the media and on the show.\nIn the 2009\u201310 season, Winfrey hosted this segment on her own. Fridays Live did not return for the show's 25th season.\n\nIn 2010, Consuelos attended the ''[[Cop Out (2010 film)|Cop Out]]'' premiere in New York where he had a pleasant conversation with [[Bryan Johnson (filmmaker)|Bryan Johnson]] in view of a spying [[Walt Flanagan]].<ref>Tell 'Em Steve-Dave! Podcast 4: Keeping Up With Consuelos</ref>\n\nIn 2012, Consuelos guest-starred on an episode of ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]'' titled \"[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit (season 13)#ep17|Justice Denied]]\". He played Michael, the prime suspect in a brutal rape during [[Fleet Week]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Rizzo|first=Carita|title=Law & Order: SVU: Mariska Will Be Back, A Tense New Case and More!|url=https://www.tvguide.com/News/Law-Order-SVU-Mariska-Hargitay-1044463.aspx|accessdate=March 5, 2012|newspaper=TV Guide|date=March 5, 2012}}</ref> Consuelos is not new to the [[Law & Order (franchise)|''Law & Order'' franchise]], he had guest-starred in the sixth-season episode \"[[Albatross (Law & Order: Criminal Intent)|Albatross]]\" of ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]]'' as the U.S. Attorney involved in a case where the judge's life is threatened.{{Citation needed|date=December 2018}}\n\nConsuelos portrayed Spivey, a recurring character, in ''[[American Horror Story (season 2)|American Horror Story: Asylum]]'', the second season of the anthology horror series.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2012/07/16/american-horror-story-mark-consuelos/ | title='American Horror Story': Mark Consuelos joins season 2 | first=Tim | last=Stack | work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] | date=July 16, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, Consuelos co-starred as Florida Senator Andy Guzman in Amazon's ''[[Alpha House]]'', a political comedy written by ''[[Doonesbury]]'' creator [[Garry Trudeau]].<ref>{{cite news | last=Goodman | first=Tim | title= Alpha House: TV Review | url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/alpha-house-tv-review-656034 | accessdate=July 24, 2014 | newspaper=The Hollywood Reporter | date=November 14, 2013}}</ref> Along with [[John Goodman]], Consuelos plays one of four Republican senators living together in a house on Capitol Hill. He has spent the summer of 2014 filming the second season.\n\nIn 2016, Consuelos landed a role on a new [[FOX]] series, ''[[Pitch (TV series)|Pitch]]'', as Oscar Arguella.<ref>{{cite news|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|title=Mark Consuelos Nabs Key Role in Fox Baseball Drama 'Pitch' (Exclusive)|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/mark-consuelos-nabs-key-role-870133|accessdate=March 25, 2018|newspaper=Hollywood Reporter|date=February 26, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Consuelos was cast in the series regular role of Hiram Lodge on [[The CW]] drama ''[[Riverdale (2017 TV series)|Riverdale]]''. His oldest son, Michael Consuelos, plays a younger Hiram Lodge starting on the second season.<ref>{{cite news|last=Petski|first=Denise|title=Mark Consuelos Joins \u2018Riverdale\u2019 For Season 2; \u2018Suits\u2019 Casts Dul\u00e9 Hill|url=https://deadline.com/2017/04/mark-consuelos-cast-riverdale-season-2-suits-dule-hill-1202077582/|accessdate=March 25, 2018|newspaper=Deadline|date=April 25, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn 1995, Consuelos met [[Kelly Ripa]], his co-star on ''[[All My Children]]''.<ref name=\"GHAMC\">{{cite magazine |last1=Friedman |first1=Megan |title=Kelly Ripa Reveals the Amazing Moment She Knew Mark Consuelos Was \"The One\" |url=https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/life/a22745812/kelly-ripa-mark-consuelos-all-my-children/ |accessdate=28 February 2019 |magazine=Good Housekeeping |date=August 16, 2018}}</ref> The two [[eloped]] on May 1, 1996.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=KellyRipa|number=329665177756762113|first=Kelly|last=Ripa|authorlink=Kelly Ripa|date=May 1, 2013|title=Omg. Here it is. 5/1/96|accessdate= November 7, 2018}}</ref> The couple has three children: Michael Joseph (born June 2, 1997), Lola Grace (born June 16, 2001) and Joaquin Antonio (born February 24, 2003).<ref>{{cite web|url= https://people.com/celebrity/kelly-ripa-all-my-children-indeed/|last=Silverman|first=Stephen M.|title=Kelly Ripa: 'All My Children,' Indeed|work=People|date=February 25, 2003|accessdate=March 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn October 3, 2008, he performed the marriage ceremony for [[Howard Stern]] and model/actress [[Beth Ostrosky]] at the Le Cirque restaurant in New York City.  The two couples had grown close, which was why Stern asked Consuelos to officiate.  Consuelos agreed, and took it upon himself to seek [[ordination]] to make it an official ceremony for Stern and Ostrosky.  The guest list for the wedding included [[Joan Rivers]], [[Barbara Walters]], [[Chevy Chase]], [[Billy Joel]] and wife [[Katie Lee (food critic)|Katie Lee]], [[Jimmy Kimmel]], [[Sarah Silverman]], and Stern's radio co-host [[Robin Quivers]].\n\nFor many years, Consuelos and Ripa lived on Crosby Street in [[SoHo, Manhattan]], but they sold that house in 2015 for $20 million and moved to a townhouse on East 76th Street.  They had bought the townhouse in 2013, though it was never officially listed on the market, from fashion designer [[Luca Orlandi]] and his wife, [[Oluchi Onweagba]], for $27 million, making it the second most expensive townhouse sold in NYC that year.<ref name=\"July17\">{{cite news |title=Kelly Ripa\u2019s Home Life Is Quite Extravagant \u2014 Find out Where the Talk Show Host Lives! |url=https://www.closerweekly.com/posts/where-does-kelly-ripa-live-136659/ |accessdate=28 February 2019 |publisher=Closer |date=July 17, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and honors==\nIn 1998 and 1999, Consuelos won the American Latino Media Arts Award for \"Outstanding Actor in a Daytime Soap Opera.\" Consuelos won \"Hottest Romance\" along with Ripa in 1997 at the Soap Opera Awards.<ref name=\"abcbio\"/> He also won the Teen's Choice Award for Choice TV Villain in 2018\n.\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''The Last Place on Earth''\n| Party Toast\n| \n|-\n| 2002\n| ''Pride & Loyalty''\n| Bill the Cop\n| \n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[The Great Raid]]''\n| Cpl. Guttierez\n| \n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[My Super Ex-Girlfriend]]''\n| Steve Velard\n| \n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Wedding Daze]]''\n| Morty\n| \n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Husband for Hire''\n| Bo/Normando\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''For the Love of Grace''\n| Steve Lockwood\n|\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Cop Out (2010 film)|Cop Out]]''\n| Manuel\n| \n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[A Walk Among the Tombstones (film)|A Walk Among the Tombstones]]''\n|Reuben\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n|''[[All We Had]]''\n| Vic\n| \n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Nine Lives (2016 film)|Nine Lives]]''\n| Ian Cox\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n|-\n| 1995\u20132010\n| ''[[All My Children]]''\n| Mateo Santos\n| 104 episodes<br>[[Soap Opera Digest Awards|Soap Opera Digest Award for Outstanding Younger Lead Actor]]<br>[[Soap Opera Digest Awards|Soap Opera Digest Award for Outstanding Male Newcomer]]<br>[[Soap Opera Digest Awards|Soap Opera Digest Award for Hottest Rom